-- European shares edge lower, Hugo Boss slips 
-- By Atul Prakash
-- Wed May 28, 2014 03:14AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, May 28 (Reuters) - European shares edged lower in early trading on Wednesday, with  Hugo Boss <BOSSn.DE> leading the market lower after Permira <PERM.UL> placed a 5.6 percent stake in the fashion group.

Hugo Boss shares fell 2.8 percent, the biggest decliner on the FTSEurofirst 300 index <.FTEU3> of top European shares after a source familiar with the transaction said on Wednesday that  shares were placed with institutional investors. [ID:nWEB00NSY]